cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.RO

This paper deals with object recognition in aerial imagery using deep neural networks and contextual information. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel dual-stream network architecture, which involves learning both local and global visual reasoning, making it relevant to the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with segmentation of buildings and roads, which falls under the sub-categories cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.RO (Robotics).
